TI  - Exploring the Evolution of Museum Knowledge Organization Systems
T2  - CATALOGING & CLASSIFICATION QUARTERLY
M3  - Article
AB  - Recent advancements in artificial intelligence (AI), particularly large language models (LLMs), have begun to transform museum practices and knowledge management systems. With robust capabilities in data integration, multimodal analysis, and knowledge generation, LLMs are reshaping museum knowledge organization systems (MKOS). This paper reviews the evolution of MKOS and examines LLM-driven innovations in three areas: metadata enhancement through human-machine collaboration, development of scalable cross-domain networks via ontology models, and dynamic, user-centric adjustments for deeper semantic connections. This paper aims to provide valuable insights into the future of MKOS in the AI-driven stage.
